post_text: The 2020 Alumni Reunion is cancelled.
shared_text:
Pioneer Alumni Reunion
May 6 at 3:20 PM ·

Good afternoon Pioneer family.

It is with sadness we announce the 2020 All Alumni Reunion is cancelled due to current government regulations and our concern for the best health and wellness for all.

Over the past few years we have really enjoyed working with so many of our local alumni and businesses to create an event for all alumni of the district where we could all make new friends and reconnect with old.

While we will miss you all, we hope to be back next year even bigger and better!

Please stay safe and remember we are all in this together and once a panther always a panther!

post_text: The Pioneer community is invited to participate in a vehicle parade in memory of Bill Landahl and to honor Kathy Landahl and family on Saturday, May 2. It will begin at the Arcade Elementary School parking lot. Cars can begin arriving at 9:30 AM. There will be fire department volunteers and police officers to organize the lineup of vehicles and also to stop traffic when the parade begins. We encourage posters with big bold letters to hang from the vehicles, flowers and notes of love and encouragement can also be tossed out of vehicles as you drive by. But absolutely NO leaving your vehicles. Due to social distancing, we need to ensure that everyone remain in their cars in the parade and continue on past the Landahl residence. Thanks!

post_text: The Physical Education teachers at Pioneer Central School at Delevan Elementary, Ms. Miller & Mr. Gertis, did a pretty neat thing Wednesday. They held a Physical Education jumping jack fitness drive-by. If students wanted to participate they had to have their parents email the teachers & include their address. From there they mapped a route of the district where they traveled 99 miles in 6 hours(!) stopping at 46 houses & seeing 53 students. They arrived at students' houses honking the car horns, and students had to come outside and show the teachers 5 of their best jumping jacks. The teachers then did 5 jumping jacks back to the kids. Library Media Specialist Jenna Driver made a highlight video at this link: https://tinyurl.com/yarsjs58

shared_text:
PTA of Delevan
April 6 at 12:18 PM ·

We know many of you have wanted this for a while. The truck delivered curbside to my home. I’m not willing to sort in my house. So, Lisa and I are outside on this gorgeous day sorting to have things ready for you. We have sanitized and prayed ourselves down. I will not be on my phone while sorting. To keep us all safe. So this post is to tell you we will be at the Delevan Elementary school today Monday April 6th from 4-8pm. If you are able to come get your items. After today’s pick up. Success or not we will post another time we are available at the school for pick up. Please be patient and kind. We are doing the best we can with what we can. PLEASE share to any Delevan Parent!!!!!

February 28 at 10:32 PM ·

Another successful Pioneer Student Art Show came to a close this evening. Thanks to all of the talented student artists and their teachers, and to all of the families and community members who came to the show this month. In addition to moving the show to the Old Fire Hall on Liberty Street, we added voting for People's Choice awards. Out of 227 votes cast, only two votes separated the first and second places. Congratulations to Meg Albino, Mackenzey Holmes and Amelia Maul! Please click on each photo for more information about the winners.
